</p>

<p corresp='TTP1816138P1' xml:id='OTP1816138P1'><rs ref='#S105737'>Phillips Co Ark</rs><lb/>
Dec 1862
</p>

<p corresp='TTP1816138P2' xml:id='OTP1816138P2'>to His Excellency<lb/>
Govenor of the State of Mississippi
</p>

<p corresp='TTP1816138P3' xml:id='OTP1816138P3'>The idea of a torpedo to destroy boats in rivers suggests that Similar Engines may be constructed &amp; sunk under a rail road track &amp; so arranged that the weight of the Locomotive car would press down the rail &amp; touch the trigger that explodes the torpedo &amp; blow the <del rend='overstrike'>engn</del> Locomotive car to attoms or off the track &amp; render the train <del rend='overstrike'>over</del> easy of capture &amp; the road dangerous &amp; uncertain for Military purposes
</p>

<p corresp='TTP1816138P4' xml:id='OTP1816138P4'>A common <del rend='overstrike'>gorden</del>^garden^ post auger would ensure to <del rend='overstrike'>S</del> excavate for the Location of the engine &amp; cuts &amp; fill the best points for location
</p>

<p corresp='TTP1816138P5' xml:id='OTP1816138P5'>If the idea is practicable its early ^use^ may save Miss many thousands &amp; much suffering
</p>

<p corresp='TTP1816138P6' xml:id='OTP1816138P6'>A graduate of the <rs ref='#S62970'>University of Miss</rs><lb/>
of class 1854
</p>


